		<title>Linx Security Raises $50M Series B to Fight Identity Risk</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/linx-security-raises-50m-series-b-to-fight-identity-risk/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Apr 2026 11:29:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=199632</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>As the enterprise perimeter keeps fragmenting into a maze of cloud services and autonomous agents, Linx Security revealed it has secured $50 million in Series B funding. Led by global</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/linx-security-raises-50m-series-b-to-fight-identity-risk/" data-wpel-link="internal">Linx Security Raises $50M Series B to Fight Identity Risk</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As the enterprise perimeter keeps fragmenting into a maze of cloud services and autonomous agents, </span><a href="https://www.linx.security/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Linx Security</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> revealed it has secured $50 million in Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/xoople-raises-130m-to-build-global-system-of-record-for-physical-change/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Led by global software investor Insight Partners, this funding round represents a crucial milestone for the NY-headquartered startup as it sets out to reinvent Identity Governance and Administration (IGA) for the AI epoch.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment round received additional investments from existing investors Cyberstarts and Index Ventures, raising the total funds invested in Linx to $83 million since its inception in 2023. The new funding will enable the company to expand globally, scale its go-to-market activities, and hasten the development of its &#8220;AI-native&#8221; identity platform.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Rise of the Machine Identity</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It&#8217;s coming at a time when old-school security controls are buckling under the strain of “identity sprawl&#8221;. Linx states that there are now over 80 non-human identities for every one of its employees, consisting of hundreds of thousands of service accounts, API keys, and autonomous AI agents. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_199634" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199634" class="size-large wp-image-199634" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Security-representation-1024x768.jpg" alt="Security representation" width="1024" height="768" /><p id="caption-attachment-199634" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Identity governance has moved from the back-office compliance function to a central plinth of enterprise security,&#8221; said CEO and co-founder of Linx Security, Israel Duanis. Old-school tools are built for a static world. Today, identities are spun up and then spun down within seconds by automatons. If you can&#8217;t see them, then you can&#8217;t secure them.&#8221; </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Industry stats tell a similar story: 90% of all security breaches involve some form of identity failure. As companies rush to deploy AI into their automated workflows, they are also unwittingly introducing vendors&#8217; thousands of &#8216;shadow&#8217; identities that slip outside the bounds of their legacy identity-gating sets of controls, allowing thieves to break in.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/xoople-raises-130m-to-build-global-system-of-record-for-physical-change/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">: Xoople Raises $130M to Build Global System of Record for Physical Change</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Enter &#8220;Linx Autopilot&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A key part of the company&#8217;s growth plan is the release of Linx Autopilot, which is described as &#8220;the first autonomous AI agent for identity governance in the industry&#8221;.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In comparison, legacy systems conduct manual periodic access reviews that often become stale by the time they are completed. Autopilot performs continuous identity behavior analysis for the organization. It recognizes mapping of relationships between human users and computable agents in real-time and pinpoints users whose permissions are overextended or dead accounts that could threaten the enterprise. It automatically remediates threats or raises issues with up-to-date context to security teams.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Market Traction and Future Outlook</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Linx Security is only three years old but already has multiple multimillion-dollar contracts with prestigious clients such as Wiz, Aramark, and numerous Fortune 500 insurance and financial services companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Linx is reinventing IGA architecture to address the come-up in agent governance,” said Teddie Wardi, managing director at Insight Partners. “They have an AI-first strategy that puts them in good standing for this important space.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Linx, with 100 employees and more to come, intends to leverage the proceeds of this Series B to further extend its footprint across EMEA and APJ. With AI agents already essential elements of the business world, Linx believes that the next era of cyber protection will not only involve safeguarding the human workforce but also managing the invisible forces of machine and code that sustain contemporary enterprise.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/linx-security-raises-50m-series-b-to-fight-identity-risk/" data-wpel-link="internal">Linx Security Raises $50M Series B to Fight Identity Risk</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
