		<title>NeuBird AI Raises $19.3M to Expand Agentic AI for Enterprise Ops</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/neubird-ai-raises-19-3m/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Clinton]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 06 Apr 2026 16:17:44 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[AI]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=199599</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Funding Boost Supports Global Expansion NeuBird AI just wrapped up a $19.3 million funding round. Xora Innovation led the investment, with backing from Mayfield, StepStone Group, Prosperity7 Ventures, and Microsoft’s</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/neubird-ai-raises-19-3m/" data-wpel-link="internal">NeuBird AI Raises $19.3M to Expand Agentic AI for Enterprise Ops</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Funding Boost Supports Global Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI just wrapped up a $19.3 million funding round. Xora Innovation led the investment, with backing from Mayfield, StepStone Group, Prosperity7 Ventures, and Microsoft’s M12 fund. Right now, enterprise IT environments are turning into a bit of a maze. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Teams juggling multi-cloud systems need to keep services running smoothly while also lowering their workload—but a lot of companies are still stuck with manual workflows for handling incidents. It’s slow and, frankly, exhausting for engineers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI says this new funding will help them speed up product development and open their platform to more DevOps, SRE, and IT operations teams. They also want to boost global sales and connect with big enterprise teams much faster.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Phil Inagaki from Xora Innovation says NeuBird AI’s results stand out for their accuracy, speed, and efficiency. Gou Rao and Vinod Jayaraman—the founders—have already built and scaled several enterprise infrastructure companies. That experience gives them a solid grasp of the problems modern teams are up against.</span></p>
<h2><b>Redefining Production Operations</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Modern enterprise IT systems generate continuous alerts, logs, and telemetry signals. Engineers spend roughly 40% of their time responding to incidents rather than building new products, according to the 2026 State of Production Reliability and AI Adoption Report.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI replaces reactive, manual workflows with an autonomous production operations agent. The platform continuously analyses telemetry data. It correlates signals across systems and delivers root cause analysis and remediation in real time.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike point solutions that only reduce alert noise, NeuBird AI acts as an always-on expert engineer. It applies domain knowledge and continuous learning to solve incidents automatically. This approach reduces alert fatigue and improves overall reliability.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Gou Rao, Co-founder and CEO, said engineering teams face mounting pressure to maintain uptime while innovating faster. “Modern infrastructure generates an unrelenting flood of alerts, logs, and telemetry signals. Most tools still require manual investigation. The result is slower innovation and lost engineering time,” he said.</span></p>
<h2><b>Introducing NeuBird AI Falcon</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI also launched NeuBird AI Falcon, its next-generation engine powering the production ops agent. Falcon extends the platform beyond incident resolution. It provides predictive risk detection and infrastructure cost optimisation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new engine delivers end-to-end production operations capabilities. Teams can prevent issues before they escalate. Engineers can reclaim time lost to manual troubleshooting and focus on higher-value work.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Vinod Jayaraman, Co-founder and CTO, said the funding will allow faster deployment of AI production ops agents into enterprise teams. “Every engineer we talk to spends most of their time responding to incidents. This productivity loss is not sustainable. NeuBird AI helps teams prevent IT issues before they escalate,” he said.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Since launching to the public in December 2024, NeuBird AI has gone from test runs to working at full scale. Customers say they&#8217;ve tackled more than a million alerts and saved over $2 million worth of engineering time. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They’re also seeing mean time to resolution drop by as much as 90%. All this shows how much NeuBird AI does for modern businesses. It boosts reliability, speeds up work, and makes day-to-day operations smoother.</span></p>
<h2><b>Strengthening Leadership and Partnerships</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_199614" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199614" class="size-full wp-image-199614" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/NeuBird-2.png" alt="An AI agent connecting with cloud platforms and executives shaking hands, symbolising leadership and enterprise partnerships." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-199614" class="wp-caption-text">NeuBird AI strengthens leadership and secures cloud partnerships to expand its enterprise AI platform globally. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI recently appointed Venkat Ramakrishnan as President and COO. He previously helped scale </span><a href="https://portworx.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Portworx </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">from Series A to acquisition. The move strengthens commercial leadership as the company expands globally.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has also earned recognition from leading cloud providers. It achieved the AWS Generative AI Competency in Generative AI Applications and Infrastructure &amp; Data. NeuBird AI joined the AWS Generative AI Accelerator and Microsoft for Startups Pegasus Program. These partnerships offer access to enterprise networks on Azure and AWS.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors emphasise NeuBird AI’s domain expertise and execution. Navin Chaddha of Mayfield praised the team’s vision and measurable customer ROI. Michelle Gonzalez of M12 highlighted the platform’s ability to operate alongside engineers in live environments. Abhishek Shukla of Prosperity7 Ventures noted that the agent allows teams to prevent issues, resolve incidents faster, and optimise systems continuously.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">John Avirett of StepStone Group said the company’s first year showed strong execution and industry traction. “NeuBird AI built an enterprise-grade AI agent, deployed it live, and delivered measurable results across industries. This reflects the strength of the technology and scale of the opportunity,” he said.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mesabi-metallics-raises-150-million/" data-wpel-link="internal">Mesabi Metallics Secures $150 Million To Advance DR-Grade Iron Ore Development</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Addressing Talent Scarcity in IT Operations</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Enterprise IT teams are struggling to find enough skilled people these days. Keeping systems running smoothly isn’t getting any easier, either—modern infrastructure is complicated, and it’s tough to keep everything reliable. Relying on manual workflows? That just slows things down and leads to more mistakes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI steps in with a smarter fix. Its agentic AI platform doesn’t just automate incident management—it actually gives teams real-time insights they can act on. Now, IT teams can stay ahead of risks, control costs, and keep systems reliable, all without piling too much work on their staff.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By reducing the need for manual intervention, NeuBird AI improves productivity and reduces burnout. Nearly 80% of companies report that up to half of their on-call engineers experience incident-related stress. The platform directly mitigates this problem, enabling engineers to focus on innovation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI’s vision positions it as a critical intelligence layer for enterprise production operations. It acts as a proactive partner alongside human teams.When companies start using the platform, they don’t just get things done faster—they actually feel more in control when handling messy, multi-cloud setups. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NeuBird AI is shaking things up with its agentic AI for enterprise IT. It makes tricky operations simpler, handles incident resolution automatically, and lets teams focus on bigger ideas instead of daily headaches. With this funding round, investors are clearly betting on the team, the tech, and the huge market ahead.</span></p>
