		<link>https://ventureburn.com/moonbounce-raises-12m-to-power-real%e2%80%91time-ai-control/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 06 Apr 2026 15:52:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=199600</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Moonbounce has announced the successful close of a $12 million funding round aimed at building its AI control engine and scaling its platform across global markets. The investment shows that</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/moonbounce-raises-12m-to-power-real%e2%80%91time-ai-control/" data-wpel-link="internal">Moonbounce Raises $12M to Power Real‑Time AI Control</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://moonbounce.io/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Moonbounce </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has announced the successful close of a $12 million </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/accuquant-secures-20-million-to-advance-ai-infrastructure/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round aimed at building its AI control engine and scaling its platform across global markets. The investment shows that more people want systems that can effectively enforce safety rules and policies as generative artificial intelligence becomes a big part of digital products.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round was co‑led by Amplify Partners and StepStone Group, with participation from angel investors including PrimeSet and Josh Leslie, former CEO of Cumulus Networks and Gremlin. Moonbounce’s leadership team includes CEO Brett Levenson, a former head of Trust &amp; Safety at Meta, and CTO Ash Bhardwaj, who previously led cloud and AI infrastructure at Apple.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Addressing the AI Moderation Challenge</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">AI products like large language models (LLMs), chatbots, and generative image models are spreading rapidly, leaving firms searching for ways to prevent a spate of unwanted behavioral toxicity, bias, misinformation, and regulatory violations. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_199602" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199602" class="size-large wp-image-199602" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/moonbounce-logo-1024x405.jpeg" alt="moonbounce logo" width="1024" height="405" /><p id="caption-attachment-199602" class="wp-caption-text">Source: moonbounce</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moonbounce’s approach centers on “policy as code&#8221;, a methodology that translates human-written content policies into structured logic that can be executed by software in real time. Moonbounce embeds explicit policy directives into its AI control engine, ensuring that decisions are predictable, consistent, and aligned with a company’s intentions, rather than relying on historical data to inflate machine learning models in hopes of teaching them what is acceptable.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/accuquant-secures-20-million-to-advance-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">AccuQuant Secures $20 Million To Advance AI Infrastructure</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">How their Technology Works</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Moonbounce uses machine learning to collect the policy rules of a company and transforms them into a form that can be assessed as the content is being produced. As content is generated by a human user or an AI model, the engine evaluates it at high speed (usually less than 300 ms) to determine whether it conforms to the given rules and takes action accordingly: block potentially damaging content, deploy a human to review it, or steer the AI system&#8217;s response toward a safer one.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In real-time moderation like this one, it points to an earlier model in queuing where moderation was left until afterwards, causing harm or risk, and then sharing it before it could be reprimanded. </span><span style="font-weight: 400">The technology used here was an eye, enacting a preventative layer as opposed to cleaning up afterwards.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Investor Confidence</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $12 million raise underscores investor belief in AI safety infrastructure as a core element of future tech stacks. Amplify Partners and StepStone Group have backed Moonbounce with an eye toward helping companies manage not just operational challenges but also reputational and regulatory exposure as AI use scales.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Levenson, Moonbounce’s CEO, has highlighted the need for systems that ensure AI behaves “predictably, every time, without exception&#8221;, emphasising that control and innovation can coexist. With the capital infusion, Moonbounce plans to enhance its product offerings, grow its engineering team, and expand go‑to‑market efforts globally.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/moonbounce-raises-12m-to-power-real%e2%80%91time-ai-control/" data-wpel-link="internal">Moonbounce Raises $12M to Power Real‑Time AI Control</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
